narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes. Anyone interested in ethnic issues in China, inner Asia, cultural anthropology and more...

I would not recommend it. Professor Hansen is an incredibly hard grader. A hard grader meaning that she seems to want to be a beacon in the History department to give low grades to show she is such a difficult teacher. The workload is quite substantial. Only take this if for some reason you a passion for Chinese Muslims.
This is the worst class that I have taken at Yale. The class time itself made very minute feel like an hour. The professor was rude. The readings were awful. Do not take it.

I would recommend this course to anyone even if they know nothing about the topic as I did not at the beginning of the course. The workload is a little higher than in some other seminars I have taken. But there is a lot of interaction with others in the class. This semester it was taught as both a graduate and undergraduate class, so there was a wider range of students with whom to interact.
